    @Beta
public abstract class AbstractSingleVariableNumericConstraintFeasibilityRegionStepSolver
extends AbstractExpressionWithPropagatedLiteralsStepSolver
    A AbstractExpressionWithPropagatedLiteralsStepSolver for a AbstractSingleVariableNumericConstraint with basic methods for determining the feasibility region of the variable, but leaving the determination of the final solution to solutionIfPropagatedLiteralsAndSplittersCNFAreSatisfied(Context).
    Author:
    braz

      • getSolutionExpressionForBoundVariable

        public abstract Expression getSolutionExpressionForBoundVariable()
        Provides the solution when the variable is bound to a value and it has already been decided that the constraint is satisfiable.

        Here are two illustrations of this method's use. If the implementation is deciding model counting, for example, this will be the expression 1, whereas if the implementation is computing the set of satisfying values, this will be one of the elements provided by the method getEquals().
